@page "/"

<PageTitle>AI Librarian</PageTitle>

<h1>AI Librarian portal</h1>

<p class="lead">
	Phase 1 portal for the Engineering pilot. Upload sources, browse what
	landed, and follow ingest progress through the audit ledger.
</p>

<div class="row g-3 mt-2">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="card h-100">
			<div class="card-body">
				<h5 class="card-title">Upload a source</h5>
				<p class="card-text">
					Push a file to <code>POST /api/portal/sources/upload</code>.
					The API stores the bytes in Blob storage, creates a
					<code>sources</code> row, and returns the new id so you
					can hand it to the ingest worker.
				</p>
				<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/upload">Open upload</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="card h-100">
			<div class="card-body">
				<h5 class="card-title">Browse sources</h5>
				<p class="card-text">
					See every source visible to your RLS context — ordered by
					most recently created. Drill in to inspect the full row,
					including the SHA-256 the worker stamped after
					canonicalization.
				</p>
				<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/sources">Browse sources</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<p class="text-muted mt-4">
	After uploading, queue ingest separately via
	<code>POST /api/ingest/enqueue</code> or MCP <code>enqueue_source</code>.
	The worker writes audit rows tagged <code>ingest/canonicalized</code>
	and <code>ingest/embedded</code> as it processes the source.
</p>
